<span id="freeTextContainer14994431777235407411">Hawk of May was the first book in this trilogy, and I enjoyed that so much that I requested this one. I didn&apos;t enjoy this one quite as much, but it was still a page-turner. Perhaps I missed the fantasy element, which is much reduced in this one.<br/><br/>Rhys is a farmer, 21, who like many little boys dreamed of becoming a warrior. When Gwalchmai seeks shelter from his father, Rhys finally works up the courage to follow his dream. He asks Gwalchmai if he can come along as servant. Most warriors start trai</span>
  <span id="freeText14994431777235407411" style="display:none">Hawk of May was the first book in this trilogy, and I enjoyed that so much that I requested this one. I didn't enjoy this one quite as much, but it was still a page-turner. Perhaps I missed the fantasy element, which is much reduced in this one.<br /><br />Rhys is a farmer, 21, who like many little boys dreamed of becoming a warrior. When Gwalchmai seeks shelter from his father, Rhys finally works up the courage to follow his dream. He asks Gwalchmai if he can come along as servant. Most warriors start training at age 7, and start fighting at 14. He is too far past that to serve as warrior. With his father's reluctant permission, Rhys leaves the holding, and starts being part of the adventure right away. <br /><br />He meets King Arthur and the rest of his Arthur's "family." He eventually continues with Gwalchmai on his mission to find and apologize to Eliden. Rhys learns first-hand that many holdings are unfriendly to Arthur and his people. <br /><br />Gwachmai's mother Morgawse is up to her plotting for Arthur's death and destruction of all Light. She is fully taken by the darkness and seeks to bring it to all the world. <br /><br />Gwalchmai is surprised to see her and his family when he goes to an unfriendly king as an emissary. They are visiting this rebellious king so that Morgawse can further her goals with another enemy of King Arthur. Gwalchmai's father Lot is a shell of his former self. His younger brother is still Morgawse's unwitting tool. She is sleeping with the resident king. Gwalchmai's death becomes her immediate and intermediate goal. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14994431777235407411" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
